  "text_preview": "\"people\" American Sign Language (ASL) ASL Lessons | Bookstore | Library | ASL University Main ► PEOPLE : The American Sign Language (ASL) sign for \"people\" The sign for \"people\" is done three or more different ways. (Pity the poor unsuspecting ASL student--especially those taking a class from a \"my way is the right way\" type of instructor). I personally use forward alternating rotational movement (as if pedaling a bicycle forward). Many of my friends and associates also use a forward rotational movement. Some of my friends and associates use a backward rotational movement. A few use an up and down alternating movement. PEOPLE: Sample sentence: PEOPLE YOU LIKE WHAT-KIND? PERSON / agent / \"one who does\" (singular) This sign, in general, means \"person.\" It can be used to mean \"one who does so"
}
